title: Boise State slides into bye slot in CFP rankings
description: Boise State, which pulled away from San Jose State last Saturday, moved ahead of BYU in the rankings released by the College Football Playoff selection committee Tuesday, putting the Broncos in position to get a first-round bye ahead of the Big 12 champ.
author: Andrea Adelson

title: Rafa's career ends: More than I believed possible
description: Rafael Nadal's incredible tennis career came to an end Tuesday as Spain lost its Davis Cup quarterfinal against the Netherlands.
author: Tom Hamilton

title: Guardiola agrees one-year extension at Man City
description: Manchester City manager Pep Guardiola agrees a one-year contract extension to take his stay at the club to 10 seasons.

title: Wales boss Bellamy savours Nations League promotion
description: Craig Bellamy hopes his successful start as Wales head coach has proved he is not the “lunatic” some expected him to be.

title: Cleveland's Darius Garland is making it impossible to overlook him
description: The Cavs guard says he doesn't get the credit he deserves, but opponents should underestimate him at their own risk.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Guardians' Stephen Vogt wins AL Manager of the Year 2 seasons after retiring as a player
description: Vogt replaced a Hall of Famer in Terry Francona. It worked out for the Guardians.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Guardiola agrees Man City contract extension
description: Pep Guardiola has agreed terms on a new one-year contract extension with Manchester City, Sky Sports News understands.

title: Bompastor offers support to Kerr after homophobic online abuse
description: Chelsea manager Sonia Bompastor has offered her full support to Sam Kerr after the striker was subjected to homophobic abuse online following the announcement she was expecting a baby with her partner, West Ham midfielder Kristie Mewis.
